lru-type.name: DRX
lru-type.description: The DTX Receiver Module (DRX), houses the Digital Deformatter (DFR) and Receiving Transponders (TRX). Its controlled and monitored by the Array Real Time Machine (ARTM). The M and C interface consists of a single CAN node.

baci-property.description: CH3 - Bit B: Alarm Status Register. Each bit is 0 for alarm since last read. 1 for No alarm. baci-property.description: THIS SHOULD BE UINT. CH3 - Bit B: Read internal sync loss counter. The accumulation of the loss of sync occurrences will be valid 10 seconds after module power-up. It is reset when the RESET_DFR_SYNC control point is called. This value can increment by up to 3 million every 48ms (if all frames are lost). If so, the 32 bit integer containing this value will overflow (roll-over) after 69 seconds. Excessively high sync rates need to be reported to the operator.

baci-property.description: CH3 - Bit B: Read internal sync status. Reports back the number of frames the data sync engine searches before a sync is established. If a suitable signal is being received on the fiber, this should take no longer than 320 frames. However, it will continue searching, and this monitor point will continue incrementing, if a suitable signal is not present. This monitor point can also be used in conjunction with the RESET_DFR_SYNC control point for verifying the performance of the search algorithm.

baci-property.description: CH3 - Bit B: Frame aligner control status. This status in conjunction with SET_DFR_FRAME_ALIGNER is used to synchronize Bits B and D with Bit C. Bit C is used as the master and the frame count for the other two bits must match Bit Cs frame count. If the frame count does not match, the frame aligner will increment or decrement the output fifo until a frame is found which matches the frame count in Bit C.
